== 概念 ==
{{Unreferenced|章节|time=2019-03-27T14:51:44+00:00}}
人具有“自己属于哪个性别的感觉，一种对自己是何種性别的自我认知”，这被称为[[性別認同|性别认同]]，大多数人都有着与[[性別指定|性别指定]]相同的性别认同，但在极少数情况下，有些人对他们的指派性别有着清晰的认识，但是并不认同这个性别的情况，有这种对性别认同不一的状态被称作性别不一致。

一般人可以很轻松的[[順性別|维持自己对出生性别的认同]]，但性別不一致者则不同。例如，在实验中让被试者尽可能快地写出尽可能多的、描述自己的语句，通常被试都会做出很多跟自己性别相关的描述。一般人做出的描述都会和其[[性别指定|性别指定]]或社会普遍认同的相应性别特征一致。而性别不一致者却会做出很多跟自己[[性别指定|性别指定]]相矛盾的描述。这种矛盾的性别认同往往会给人以严重的痛苦体验。

在过去，一般认为性别是由生殖器和染色体所决定的，并一直认为这和性别认同是一回事，但是解剖学上也有发现染色体与性腺所不同的性分化异常的情况。性别不一致被认为是一种指派性别与涉及大脑性别认同的部分因故彼此不匹配的情况。

性别不一致与性倾向无关。性别不一致者可能会认为自己是异性恋、男同性恋、女同性恋或双性恋。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Gender dysphoria|url=https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/gender-dysphoria/|access-date=2022-01-07|date=2017-10-23|work=英国国家医疗服务体系（NHS）|language=en|archive-date=2020-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320050603/https://www.nhs.uk/conditions/gender-dysphoria/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==症状==
一个人感觉到的性别与被分配的性别（通常在出生时）不一致而产生的困扰是性别不一致的主要症状<ref>{{cite journal|title=Gender Dysphoria in Adults|first1=Kenneth J.|last2=Lawrence|first2=Anne A.|journal=Annual Review of Clinical Psychology|doi=10.1146/annurev-clinpsy-021815-093034|year=2016|volume=12|pages=217–247|pmid=26788901|quote=[For DSM-5] a reconceptualization was articulated in which 'identity' per se was not considered a sign of a mental disorder. Rather, it was the incongruence between one’s felt gender and assigned sex/gender (usually at birth) leading to distress and/or impairment that was the core feature of the diagnosis.|last3=Kreukels|first3=Baudewijntje P.C.|last1=Zucker}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Gender Dysphoria: Two Steps Forward, One Step Back|first1=Arlene Istar|journal=Clinical Social Work Journal|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10615-013-0447-0|year=2013|volume=41|pages=288–296|quote=[Despite some misgivings], I think that the change in nomenclature from the DSM-IV to the DSM-5 is a step forward, that is, removing the concept of gender as the site of the disorder and placing the focus on issues of distress and dysphoria.|last1=Lev|s2cid=144556484}}</ref>。

出生时被分配为男性的人的性别不一致（通常被称为AMAB）倾向于遵循两种广泛的轨迹之一：早发或晚发。早发的性别不一致在童年时行为上就很明显。有时，这一群体的性别不一致会停止一段时间，他们会在一段时间内认同为同性恋者，然后再复发性别不一致。这类人在成年后通常会被其出生时的性别所吸引，通常被认定为异性恋。迟发的性别不一致并不包括早期儿童时期的明显迹象，但有些人报告说，他们在童年时曾有过成为异性的愿望，但没有向他人报告。<ref name="Guillamon">{{cite journal|title=A Review of the Status of Brain Structure Research in Transsexualism|date=October 2016|journal=Archives of Sexual Behavior|issue=7|doi=10.1007/s10508-016-0768-5|volume=45|pages=1615–48|pmc=4987404|pmid=27255307|vauthors=Guillamon A, Junque C, Gómez-Gil E}}</ref>出生时被分配为男性的人，如果有迟发的性别不一致，通常会因性兴奋而变装。<ref name="dsm5">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/451|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing|year=2013|isbn=978-0-89042-554-1|edition=Fifth|location=Arlington, VA|pages=[https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/451 451–460]}}</ref>出生时被分配为男性的的跨性别者，如果经历晚发的性别不一致，通常会被女性所吸引，并可能被认定为女同性恋或双性恋者，而早发的通常会被男性所吸引。<ref name="Guillamon" />类似的模式也发生在出生时被分配为女性的人（AFAB）身上，经历早发的性别不一致的人最有可能被女性吸引，而晚发的人最有可能被男性吸引并被认定为同性恋。<ref name="Guillamon" />在AFABs中，早发的性别不一致是最常见的。<ref name="Guillamon" /><ref name="dsm5" />

性別不一致兒童通常有以下情况：喜欢异性典型的玩具、游戏或活动；讨厌自己的生殖器；以及非常喜欢异性玩伴。<ref name="DSM52">{{cite book|author1=American Psychiatry Association|url=https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/451|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5)|date=2013|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing|isbn=978-0-89042-555-8|edition=5th|location=Washington, DC and London|pages=[https://archive.org/details/diagnosticstatis0005unse/page/451 451–460]}}</ref>一些儿童也可能经历与与同龄層的社会隔离，焦虑，孤独和抑郁。<ref name=":2">{{Cite book|title=A Nurse's Guide to Women's Mental Health|last=Davidson|first=Michelle R.|publisher=Springer Publishing Company|year=2012|isbn=0826171133|page=114}}</ref>据[[美國心理學會|美國心理學會]]称，跨性别儿童比其他儿童更容易在学校，寄养，住宿治疗中心，无家可归者中心和少年司法方案中遭受骚扰和暴力。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Cisgenderism in psychology: pathologising and misgendering children from 1999 to 2008|first1=Y. Gavriel|last2=Hegarty|first2=Peter|journal=Psychology and Sexuality|issue=2|doi=10.1080/19419899.2011.576696|year=2012|volume=3|pages=137–60|last1=Ansara}}</ref>

在青少年和成年人中，症状包括渴望成为另一性别并被当作另一性别对待。<ref name="DSM52" />成年性别不一致者面临更大的压力、孤独、焦虑、抑郁、自卑和自杀风险。<ref name=":2" />跨性别者还面临饮食失调<ref>{{cite journal|title=Gender Identity, Sexual Orientation, and Eating-Related Pathology in a National Sample of College Students|date=August 2015|journal=The Journal of Adolescent Health|issue=2|doi=10.1016/j.jadohealth.2015.03.003|volume=57|pages=144–9|pmc=4545276|pmid=25937471|vauthors=Diemer EW, Grant JD, Munn-Chernoff MA, Patterson DA, Duncan AE}}<!--|access-date=May 10, 2015--></ref>和药物滥用<ref>Harmon, A., & Oberleitner, M. G. (2016). Gender dysphoria. In Gale (Ed.), Gale encyclopedia of children's health: Infancy through adolescence (3rd ed.). Farmington, MI: Gale.</ref>的高风险。

在許多案例中性別不一致通常是在小時候就會出現，但也有在[[青春期|青春期]]或成人時才出現的可能，並且隨著年紀增長而越來越強烈<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gendertalk.com/articles/oped/gid_tnt.shtml |title=Dorlands Medical Dictionary |access-date=2007-05-26 |archive-date=2013-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130324063906/http://www.gendertalk.com/articles/oped/gid_tnt.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。由於許多文化並無法接受跨性別的行為，這種感覺往往為當事人以其家人、朋友帶來許多問題。在許多案例的報告中，也有人的不適感是覺得自己的身體「出了差錯」，或從一開始就不應該是如此。
以下症状一般被认为是性別不一致的表现。但这些症状并非所有性别不一致者都有表现。

==原因==
{{refimprove section|time=2019-07-26}}
{{Main article|跨性別成因}}
当一个人因[[性別認同|性别认同]]而感到不满时，性别不一致就会存在，从而导致他们情绪低落。<ref>Davidson, Michelle R. (2012). A Nurse's Guide to Women's Mental Health. Springer Publishing Company. p. 114. ISBN 0826171133</ref>研究人员对性別不一致者的痛苦和损伤的本质持不同意见。一些研究人员认为，性别不一致者受苦是因为他们受到羞辱和暴力。<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Politics of Pathology and the Making of Gender Identity Disorder|last=Bryant|first=Karl Edward|publisher=ProQuest Dissertations & Theses (PQDT)|year=2007|isbn=9780549268161|location=Ann Arbor, Michigan|page=222}}</ref>而且，如果社会性别分化不那么严格，跨性別就会遭受少一點的痛苦。<ref>Giordano, Simona (2012). Children with Gender Identity Disorder: A Clinical, Ethical, and Legal Analysis. New Jersey: Routledge. p. 147. ISBN 0415502713.
</ref>

性别不一致的确切成因尚未明确。<ref name=":0" />有研究证据表明，遗传因素在性别不一致的发展中起主要作用<ref name="heylens et al2">{{cite journal|title=Gender identity disorder in twins: a review of the case report literature|date=March 2012|journal=The Journal of Sexual Medicine|issue=3|doi=10.1111/j.1743-6109.2011.02567.x|volume=9|pages=751–7|pmid=22146048|quote=Of 23 [[Twin#Monozygotic_(identical)_twins|monozygotic]] female and male twins, nine (39.1%) were concordant for GID; in contrast, none of the 21 same‐sex dizygotic female and male twins were concordant for GID, a statistically significant difference (P = 0.005)... These findings suggest a role for genetic factors in the development of GID.|author3-link=Kenneth Zucker|vauthors=Heylens G, De Cuypere G, Zucker KJ, Schelfaut C, Elaut E, Vanden Bossche H, De Baere E, T'Sjoen G}}</ref><ref name="diamond-20132">{{cite journal|title=Transsexuality Among Twins: Identity Concordance, Transition, Rearing, and Orientation|last=Diamond|first=Milton|journal=International Journal of Transgenderism|issue=1|doi=10.1080/15532739.2013.750222|year=2013|volume=14|pages=24–38|quote=Combining data from the present survey with those from past-published reports, 20% of all male and female monozygotic twin pairs were found concordant for transsexual identity... The responses of our twins relative to their rearing, along with our findings regarding some of their experiences during childhood and adolescence show their identity was much more influenced by their genetics than their rearing.|author-link=Milton Diamond|s2cid=144330783}}</ref>，性别认同被认为可能反映了生物、环境和文化因素的复杂相互作用。<ref name="Rosenthal-2014">{{Cite journal|title=Approach to the Patient: Transgender Youth: Endocrine Considerations|last=Rosenthal|first=Stephen M.|date=2014-12-01|journal=The Journal of Clinical Endocrinology & Metabolism|issue=12|doi=10.1210/jc.2014-1919|volume=99|pages=4379–4389|language=en|issn=0021-972X|pmid=25140398|doi-access=free}}</ref>

== 社会行动 ==
《中华人民共和国未成年人保护法》（2020年修订）规定，学校、幼儿园应当对未成年人进行适龄性教育。接纳人人在性取向、性别认同和性别表达方面享有平等的选择权，不遭受污名、歧视和暴力，是全面性教育的重要内容之一。儿童和青少年对性和性别多元的理解将有助于他们理解与识别和社会性别有关的歧视和偏见，培养宽容和尊重的价值观，学会接纳自己和他人，并进一步创造一个更友好的社会。<ref>联合国教育、科学及文化组织．国际性教育技术指导纲要．北京：联合国教育、科学及文化组织，2017：22,42-75</ref>

== 診斷 ==

=== ICD-10 ===
根據《[[國際疾病與相關健康問題統計分類|國際疾病與相關健康問題統計分類]]》第十版（1993），列出與性別認同有關的幾種疾病：<ref name="ICD-10">{{cite web|title=International Classification of Diseases (ICD) F64 Gender identity disorders|url=http://apps.who.int/classifications/icd10/browse/2016/en#/F60-F69|accessdate=9 August 2018|publisher=[[World_Health_Organization|World Health Organization]]|archive-date=2017-02-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170208033519/http://apps.who.int/classifications/icd10/browse/2016/en#/F60-F69|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Classification of sexual disorders|last=Potts|first=S|last2=Bhugra|first2=D|journal=[[International_Review_of_Psychiatry|International Review of Psychiatry]]|issue=2|doi=10.3109/09540269509028323|year=1995|volume=7|pages=167–174}}</ref>
* [[變性|易性症]]（F64.0）：渴望成為及被接受為相反性別的成員，通常伴隨著[[性別重置手術|性別重置手術]]和激素治療的慾望。
* 兒童性別認同障礙（F64.2）：一個人對於自身的[[指定性別|指定性別]]而持續強烈的痛苦，並且在青春期之前表現出來。
* 其他性別認同障礙（F64.8）
* 性別認同障礙，不明確（F64.9）
* [[性成熟障礙|性成熟障礙]]（F66.0）：關於一個人的[[性別認同|性別認同]]或[[性取向|性取向]]的不確定性，導致焦慮或痛苦。<ref>{{cite web|title=International Classification of Diseases|url=http://www.who.int/health-topics/international-classification-of-diseases|accessdate=11 August 2018|publisher=World Health Organization|archive-date=2018-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902025504/http://www.who.int/health-topics/international-classification-of-diseases|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== DSM-IV ===
根據《[[精神疾病診斷與統計手冊|精神疾病診斷與統計手冊]]》第四版（1994），要被診斷判定為「性別認同障礙」前，須達到五項條件：
<ref>[http://www.behavenet.com/capsules/disorders/genderiddis.htm Diagnostic criteria for Gender Identity Disorder] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070621162502/http://www.behavenet.com/capsules/disorders/genderiddis.htm|date=2007-06-21}} - DSM-IV & DSM-IV (TR)</ref>

* 必須要有證據顯示有強烈且持續的跨性別認同感。
* 跨性別認同感不可以是因為認為另一種性別在文化上有更多優勢而產生的。
* 同時也必須要有證據顯示對於天生的性別有持續性的不適應感，或是無法適應自己所屬性別的[[性別角色|性別角色]]。
* 當事人不可同時擁有身體上的雙性人狀態（例如{{tsl|en|Androgen Insensitivity Syndrome|睾脂酮不敏症候族}}或[[先天性腎上腺增生症|先天性腎上腺增生症]]）。
* 必須要有臨床上的證據能顯示當事人在社交、工作或其他重要領域上遭遇顯著的挫折或傷害。

=== DSM-5 ===
根據《[[精神疾病診斷與統計手冊|精神疾病診斷與統計手冊]]》第五版（2013），要被診斷判定為「性別不安」前，[[青少年|青少年]]或[[成人|成人]]須至少符合兩個標準以及持續至少六個月：<ref name="DSM5">{{cite book|author1=American Psychiatry Association|title=Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM-5)|date=2013|publisher=American Psychiatric Publishing|location=Washington, DC and London|isbn=0-89042-555-8|pages=451–460|edition=5th}}</ref>
<!--Note that these are paraphrased from the original to avoid copyright violation.-->
* 強烈渴望成為自身[[指定性別|指定性別]]以外的性別。
* 強烈希望被視為自身[[指定性別|指定性別]]以外的性別。
* 自身[[性別特徵|性別特徵]]與[[性別表達|性別表達]]經歷之間存在顯著的不一致。
* 強烈渴望自身[[指定性別|指定性別]]以外的[[性別特徵|性別特徵]]。
* 由於自身[[性別特徵|性別特徵]]與[[性別表達|性別表達]]經歷不一致而強烈希望擺脫它。
* 堅信一個人具有與自身[[指定性別|指定性別]]不同的典型性別的反應和感受。

此外，該病症必須與臨床上顯著的痛苦或損害相關。<ref name="DSM5" />

DSM-5將性別不安從[[性偏離|性偏離]]中移除，並將其納入其他的類別。<ref name="DSM5" />在性別認同障礙被批評為污名後，該診斷被重新命名為性別不安，<ref name="DSMVChild">{{cite web|title=Gender Dysphoria in Children|url=http://www.dsm5.org/ProposedRevision/Pages/proposedrevision.aspx?rid=192#|accessdate=July 3, 2011|date=May 4, 2011|publisher=American Psychiatric Association|archive-date=2012-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314204820/http://www.dsm5.org/ProposedRevision/Pages/proposedrevision.aspx?rid=192|dead-url=no}}</ref>並刪除了子類別中的[[性取向|性取向]]。[[兒童|兒童]]的診斷與[[成人|成人]]的診斷被分開，如「[[兒童性別不安|兒童性別不安]]」。為兒童建立一種特定的診斷反映了兒童較少有能力洞察他們正在經歷的事情，或者讓他們表達自身正在經歷的事情。<ref>{{cite web|title=P 00 Gender Dysphoria in Children|url=http://www.dsm5.org/ProposedRevision/Pages/proposedrevision.aspx?rid=192#|accessdate=April 2, 2012|publisher=American Psychiatric Association|archive-date=2012-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314204820/http://www.dsm5.org/ProposedRevision/Pages/proposedrevision.aspx?rid=192|dead-url=no}}</ref>如果一個人不符合性別不安的標準但仍有臨床上顯著的痛苦或損傷，則可以診斷出「其他性別不安」或「性別不安，不明確」。<ref name="DSM5" />

=== ICD-11 ===
根據《[[國際疾病與相關健康問題統計分類|國際疾病與相關健康問題統計分類]]》第十一版（2019），對性別認同相關疾病的分類進行重大修訂。<ref>{{cite web|title=International Classification of Diseases|url=http://www.who.int/health-topics/international-classification-of-diseases|publisher=World Health Organization|access-date=August 11, 2018|archive-date=2018-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902025504/http://www.who.int/health-topics/international-classification-of-diseases|dead-url=no}}</ref> {{as of|2018|08}}，ICD-11這種情況列為「性別不一致」。<ref name="icd11-gc">{{cite web|title=Gender incongruence (ICD-11)|url=https://icd.who.int/browse11/l-m/en#/http://id.who.int/icd/entity/411470068|publisher=WHO|website=icd.who.int|access-date=August 28, 2018|archive-date=2018-08-01|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180801205234/https://icd.who.int/browse11/l-m/en%23/http://id.who.int/icd/entity/294762853#/http://id.who.int/icd/entity/411470068|dead-url=no}}</ref>

* 青春期或成年期性別不一致（HA60)：取代 F64.0
* 童年期性別不一致（HA61)：取代 F64.2
* 未特指的性別不一致（HA6Z)：取代 F64.9

在ICD-11中，由于缺乏公共卫生或临床意义，[[雙重角色異裝癖|双重角色异装癖]]被移除。<ref name="Reed_et_al._(2016)">{{cite journal|title=Disorders related to sexuality and gender identity in the ICD-11: revising the ICD-10 classification based on current scientific evidence, best clinical practices, and human rights considerations|date=October 2016|journal=World Psychiatry|issue=3|doi=10.1002/wps.20354|volume=15|pages=205–221|pmc=5032510|pmid=27717275|quote=The ICD‐10 classification of Sexual dysfunctions (F52) is based on a Cartesian separation of “organic” and “non‐organic” conditions.|ref={{harvid|Reed et al.|2016}}|display-authors=6|vauthors=Reed GM, Drescher J, Krueger RB, Atalla E, Cochran SD, First MB, Cohen-Kettenis PT, Arango-de Montis I, Parish SJ, Cottler S, Briken P, Saxena S}}</ref>此外，已經移除了[[性成熟障礙|性成熟障礙]]。<ref name="pmid27717275">{{cite journal|title=Disorders related to sexuality and gender identity in the ICD-11: revising the ICD-10 classification based on current scientific evidence, best clinical practices, and human rights considerations|date=October 2016|journal=World Psychiatry|issue=3|doi=10.1002/wps.20354|volume=15|pages=205–221|pmc=5032510|pmid=27717275|vauthors=Reed GM, Drescher J, Krueger RB, Atalla E, Cochran SD, First MB, Cohen-Kettenis PT, Arango-de Montis I, Parish SJ, Cottler S, Briken P, Saxena S}}</ref>

在ICD-11中，其解釋類似於DSM-V的定義，但不需要明顯的痛苦或損害。<ref name="icd11-gc" />

在ICD-10中，按照当时的惯例，性别认同障碍被列入精神障碍一章。在整个20世纪，ICD和DSM都从精神病理学的角度探讨了跨性别，因为跨性别呈现出某人的[[性別指定|性别指定]]和他们的[[性別認同|性别认同]]之间的差异。由于这可能导致精神痛苦，因此被认为是一种精神障碍，痛苦或不适是核心诊断特征。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Minding the body: situating gender identity diagnoses in the ICD-11|url=https://www.academia.edu/12557295|date=December 2012|journal=International Review of Psychiatry|issue=6|doi=10.3109/09540261.2012.741575|volume=24|pages=568–77|pmid=23244612|quote=Until the middle of the 20th century, with rare exceptions, transgender presentations were usually classified as psychopathological.|vauthors=Drescher J, Cohen-Kettenis P, Winter S|s2cid=12805083|access-date=2022-01-08|archive-date=2022-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108034909/https://www.academia.edu/12557295|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=The DSM diagnostic criteria for gender identity disorder in adolescents and adults|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/38019925|date=April 2010|journal=Archives of Sexual Behavior|issue=2|doi=10.1007/s10508-009-9562-y|volume=39|pages=499–513|pmid=19838784|quote=The DSM has consistently approached gender problems from the position that a divergence between the assigned sex or “the” physical sex (assuming that “physical sex” is a one-dimensional construct) and “the” psychological sex (gender) per se signals a psychiatric disorder. Although the terminology and place of the gender identity disorders in the DSM have varied in the different versions, the distress about one’s assigned sex has remained, since DSM-III, the core feature of the diagnosis.|vauthors=Cohen-Kettenis PT, Pfäfflin F|s2cid=16336939}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|first=Anne A.|last=Lawrence|name-list-style=vanc|chapter=Gender Dysphoria|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Q8hTDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA634|editor-first1=Deborah C.|editor-last1=Beidel|editor-first2=B. Christopher|editor-last2=Frueh|date=2018|title=Adult Psychopathology and Diagnosis|edition=8th|page=634|publisher=[[Wiley_(publisher)|John Wiley & Sons]]|isbn=978-1-119-38360-4|quote=The World Professional Association for Transgender Health (WPATH), for example, defined {{abbr|GD|Gender Dysphoria}} as “discomfort or distress that is caused by a discrepancy between a person’s gender identity and that person’s sex assigned at birth (and the associated gender role and/or primary and secondary sex characteristics)”|access-date=2022-01-08|archive-date=2022-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108034908/https://books.google.com/books?id=Q8hTDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA634|dead-url=no}}</ref>在2000年代和2010年代，这种观念受到了越来越多的挑战，因为一些人认为将跨性别视为一种精神障碍是一种耻辱。有人认为，[[跨性別者|跨性别者]]的痛苦和功能障碍应被视为社会对具有性别差异外表和行为的个人的排斥、歧视和（性）暴力的结果，这样做更为恰当。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Removing transgender identity from the classification of mental disorders: a Mexican field study for ICD-11|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lanpsy/article/PIIS2215-0366(16)30165-1/fulltext|date=September 2016|journal=The Lancet. Psychiatry|issue=9|doi=10.1016/S2215-0366(16)30165-1|volume=3|pages=850–9|pmid=27474250|vauthors=Robles R, Fresán A, Vega-Ramírez H, Cruz-Islas J, Rodríguez-Pérez V, Domínguez-Martínez T, Reed GM|access-date=2022-01-08|archive-date=2021-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210705044007/https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lanpsy/article/PIIS2215-0366(16)30165-1/fulltext|dead-url=no}}</ref>研究表明，跨性别者比其他人群更有可能出现心理健康问题，但针对跨性别者的健康服务往往不足或不存在。由于通常需要一个正式的ICD代码来获得治疗和报销，世界卫生组织认为将跨性别从ICD-11中全部删除是不明智的。因此，决定将这一概念从精神障碍章节移至新的性健康章节。<ref name="Reed_et_al._(2016)" />

== 治疗 ==
诊断为性别不一致的治疗可能包括心理咨询、支持患者的性别表达、激素治疗或手术。这可能涉及到医疗干预（如激素治疗、生殖器手术、电解或激光脱毛、胸部/乳房手术或其他重建手术）导致的身体过渡。<ref name=":0" />治疗的目标可能仅仅是减少患者跨性别状态引起的问题，例如：为患者提供咨询，以减少与变装相关的内疚感。<ref name="Leiblum-2006">{{Cite book|last=Leiblum|first=Sandra|title=Principles and Practice of Sex Therapy, Fourth Edition|publisher=The Guilford Press|year=2006|isbn=978-1-59385-349-5|pages=488–9}}</ref>

已有机构制定了指导方针来帮助临床医生。世界跨性别人士健康专业协会（WPATH）的护理标准被一些临床医生用作治疗指南。治疗指南通常遵循“减少伤害”模式。<ref name="AAP">{{cite journal|title=Office-based care for lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and questioning youth|date=July 2013|journal=Pediatrics|issue=1|doi=10.1542/peds.2013-1282|volume=132|pages=198–203|pmid=23796746|quote=However, adolescents with multiple or anonymous partners, having unprotected intercourse, or having substance abuse issues should be tested at shorter intervals.|author1=Committee On Adolescence|doi-access=free}}</ref><ref name="GLMA">{{cite web|title=www.glma.org Compendium of Health Profession Association LGBT Policy & Position Statements|url=http://www.glma.org/_data/n_0001/resources/live/GLMA%20Compendium%20of%20Health%20Profession%20Association%20LGBT%20Policy%20and%20Position%20Statements.pdf|access-date=August 27, 2013|year=2013|publisher=GLMA|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109071446/http://www.glma.org/_data/n_0001/resources/live/GLMA%20Compendium%20of%20Health%20Profession%20Association%20LGBT%20Policy%20and%20Position%20Statements.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="APA">{{cite web|title=APA Policy Statements on Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, & Transgender Concerns|url=http://www.apa.org/about/policy/booklet.pdf|access-date=August 27, 2013|year=2011|publisher=American Psychological Association|quote=BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that APA recognizes the efficacy, benefit, and necessity of gender transition treatments for appropriately evaluated individuals and calls upon public and private insurers to cover these medically necessary treatments;|archive-date=2022-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121154251/https://www.apa.org/about/policy/booklet.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

